  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Start preparing the potatoes</strong></p>\n<p>Boil a kettle.</p>\n<p>Peel and chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces.</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook the potatoes</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat. Bring to the boil and cook for 10-15 minutes or until fork-tender.</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return them to the pot.</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare the feta skordalia</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely grate the<strong> garlic</strong>.</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half.</p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks (keep the chopped leaves and stalks separate!) and set aside for later.</p>\n<p>Mash the <strong>feta</strong> with a fork until smooth. Re-boil a kettle.</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook the diced chorizo </strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat.</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced chorizo</strong> and cook for 5-6 minutes or until starting to crisp.</p>\n<p>Once starting to crisp, transfer the <strong>chorizo</strong> and<strong> oil</strong> to a plate and reserve for later.</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1585.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Finish making the feta skordalia</strong></p>\n<p>Return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat.</p>\n<p>Add 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong>,<strong> </strong>2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil, </strong>the<strong> grated garlic </strong>(Don't like raw garlic? Go easy!) and <strong>mashed feta </strong>and mash until smooth.</p>\n<p>Once done, cover to keep warm and set aside until serving – this is your <strong>feta skordalia</strong>.</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 5,
